2. Selection Sort
Definition

Find the smallest element and place it at the beginning.

Java Code
public class SelectionSort {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int arr[] = {5, 3, 8, 4, 2};

        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length - 1; i++) {
            int min = i;

            for (int j = i + 1; j < arr.length; j++) {
                if (arr[j] < arr[min])
                    min = j;
            }

            int temp = arr[i];
            arr[i] = arr[min];
            arr[min] = temp;
        }

        for (int num : arr)
            System.out.print(num + " ");
    }
}

Output

2 3 4 5 8

Time Complexity

Best: O(n²)
Average: O(n²)
Worst: O(n²)

Space Complexity

O(1)